'''St. James Academy''' is the newest [[Roman Catholic Church|Catholic]] [[high school]] in the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kansas City in Kansas]]. Located in [[Lenexa, Kansas]], it is the city's first and only Catholic high school. St. James Academy is currently in its twelfth academic year of existence. It is located directly off Prairie Star Parkway and K7. The school was established in 2005 by the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Kansas City in Kansas]] and was named after [[St. James the Greater]]. The campus was named after Archbishop Emeritus James Patrick Keleher. The school colors are navy, crimson, and silver. St. James Academy has an average annual enrollment of around 900 students.
==Extracurricular activities==
===Athletics=== St. James Academy offers a variety of sports for the students. They are classified as a 5A school, according to [[KSHSAA]].<ref name="Sports">[http://www.sjakeepingfaith.org/index.php/student-life/athletics SJA Sports]</ref>
